Police are searching for a man, aged between 25 and 30 years, after he stabbed someone at the Engen garage on the corners of De Wet and Klip roads in Lotus River on Wednesday 4 January at about 17:30. The stab victim died due to blood loss.Grassy Park police spokesperson Constable Carol Strauss says: A 23-year-old man from Ottery was stabbed in the right buttock. The suspect was last seen wearing a blue t-shirt and orange shorts. The suspect is still at large and the police request anyone with information regarding the matter to please come forward. V Anyone with information can call the police on Crime Stop at 08600 10111.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.